    • Method Detail

      • create

        public static AdobeAssetIllustratorFile create(java.lang.String name,
                                               AdobeAssetFolder parentFolder,
                                               java.util.ArrayList<AdobeAssetFile> images,
                                               boolean overwrite,
                                               IAdobeGenericRequestCallback<AdobeAssetIllustratorFile,com.adobe.creativesdk.foundation.internal.utils.AdobeCSDKException> responseCallback,
                                               android.os.Handler callBackRequiredForHandler)
        Creates an Illustrator file asynchronously.
        Parameters:
        name - the name of the file to create.
        parentFolder - the name of the AdobeAssetFolder containing the AI file to be created.
        images - an array of AdobeAssetFile objects for the creation of the AdobeAssetIllustratorFile. These objects have to be SVG files without external references that may contain base64 encoded JPEG or PNG images. (Currently only the first array object is used).
        overwrite - whether to allow overwriting an existing destination file. Set to NO if the file doesn't exist.
        responseCallback - track the progress of file creation, completion, progress, error, cancellation.
        callBackRequiredForHandler - optional parameter. If not null the callback gets posted on the handler event queue
        Returns:
        a place holder pointer to the AdobeAssetIllustratorFile.
